This product is the defensive, detector-only tool ("scan -> classify -> scrub")
accompanying the paper:

  "Channel Location Constrains the Auditability of Subliminal Learning"
  (citation details in CITATION.cff).

The runnable trait-installation / sufficiency construction studied in that paper
is withheld from this release for responsible disclosure (see the reproducibility
artifact's redaction note). This tool installs no trait; it detects, classifies,
and removes vocabulary-channel leakage in an already-trained student model.

This software depends on, but does not include, third-party libraries (PyTorch,
Hugging Face Transformers) and external model checkpoints, each distributed under
its own license.
